27/02/2004
TIRANA, Albania -- Foreign Minister Kastriot Islami delivered a speech Thursday (26 February) before the OSCE Permanent Council in Vienna, insisting that integration into Euro-Atlantic structures remains the government's priority, along with regional stability and co-operation. 
He added that Albania plans to conclude talks on the Stabilisation and Association Agreement with the EU by the end of this year and said Albania expects a clear message regarding NATO membership at the Alliance's June summit in Istanbul.
In other news, Albania's Helsinki Committee praised President Alfred Moisiu's initiative to amend the electoral law and improve the election infrastructure. 
The committee recommended that a large team of experts assist the bipartisan commission and parliament in drafting and approving changes to the electoral code. 
(ATA - 26/02/04)
